Number: 1443Date: 14-Jun-84 16':47':35Submitter: Sannella.PASource: Masinter.paSubject: New Pagefault hooks': \PFAULT.INTERRUPT and \PFAULT.INTERRUPT.FREQUENCYLisp Version: Description: 'Date':  7 Jun 84 15':52 PDT'From': Masinter.pa'Subject': \PFAULT.INTERRUPT and \PFAULT.INTERRUPT.FREQUENCY'To': vanMelle'cc': LispSupport'''I added a \PFAULT.INTERRUPT feature which allows a function to get called whenever there is a page fault (except when there are stack problems, etc. It is a one-shot': if \PFAULT.INTERRUPT is non-NIL, it gets a \CAUSEINTERRUPT and then \PFAULT.INTERRUPT gets set to NIL (thats so the interrupt routine can fault itself if necessary.)''I intend to use this for SPYing on pagefaults.''Workaround: Test Case: Edit-By: Edit-Date: Attn: Assigned To: In/By: Disposition: System: Operating SystemSubsystem: Virtual MemoryMachine: Disk: Microcode Version: Memory Size: File Server: Server Software Version: Difficulty: Frequency: EverytimeImpact: Priority: Status: FixedProblem Type: Source Files: 